Kenyans ushered in the New Year in style amid tight security in Mombasa.Various entertainment joints and hotels hosted the New Year celebrations with fireworks limited to only 12 joints that had successfully applied for the permit from the Mombasa government. The Kenya Navy and Kenya Wildlife Services officers patrolled the sea, while more than 4,000 other police and Mombasa inspectorate officers were stationed at various entertainment joints, malls, churches and other crowded places. Sea patrols were particularly more intense.President Uhuru Kenyatta earlier met Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery who briefed him about the security arrangements at the Serena Hotel at 3pm. Uhuru later joined leaders at State House, Mombasa, to usher in the New Year.He urged Kenyans to preach peace and embrace each other as brothers and sisters.